def: Correction or alteration by writing between the lines;interlineation. Bp. Burnet.
To choose; to select. [Obs.] "Wailed wine and meats." Henryson.
One of a Mohammedan sect founded in the ninth century byKarmat.
Carnal copulation in a manner against nature; buggery. Gen.xix. 5.

A ceasing of discontinuance, as of action, whether termporaryor final; a stop; as, a cessation of the war.The temporary cessation of the papal iniquities. Motley.The day was yearly observed for a festival by cessation from labor.Sir J. Hayward.Cessation of arms (Mil.), an armistice, or truce, agreed to by thecommanders of armies, to give time for a capitulation, or for otherpurposes.
A division of Mammalia in which the placenta is zonelike.
Fighting in the bush, or from behind bushes, trees, orthickets.

Of or pertaining to the thorax, or chest. Thoracic duct(Anat.), the great trunk of the lymphatic vessels, situated on theventral side of the vertebral column in the thorax and abdomen. SeeIllust. of Lacteal.
Worthy of meed, reward, or recompense; meritorious. "Meedfulworks." Wiclif.
Not gilded; hence, not rewarded with gold.
